<font color="#FF0000">TO ANDY AND DOC DEL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun  3 22:32:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Andy and Doc Del,<br><br>
As I turn over my thoughts in response to your comments, I find mistrust at the core. It is my lack of trust in the motives of those attemping this &quot;change&quot; in Vietnam that spark my feelings.<br><br>
These feelings are very strong. I cannot deny them. I feel very strongly that those who died ARE being dishonored.<br><br>
On the other hand, your thoughts that this is just an alternative way to achieve the goal at which we failed as a country so long ago is an alternative view which I will give my utmost consideration. I have to work it through. Intellectually, I can see where you may be right. Emotionally, I must be sure it is right for me.<br>
Practically, it seems a more postitive view.<br>
Realistically, I don't know where I'll wind up. <br><br>
This is one hell of a see-saw, isn't it?<br><br>
Thanks to both of you. You have me thinking!<br><br>
I'll be back on this.<br><br>
Art  <br><br>

